title: Google\Cloud\Trace\V2\StackTrace\StackFrame
name: StackFrame
description:
Represents a single stack frame in a stack trace.

Generated from protobuf message google.devtools.cloudtrace.v2.StackTrace.StackFrame

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.function_name
params.description: The fully-qualified name that uniquely identifies the function or method that is active in this frame (up to 1024 bytes).

params.name: data.original_function_name
params.description: An un-mangled function name, if function_name is mangled. The name can be fully-qualified (up to 1024 bytes).

params.name: data.file_name
params.description: The name of the source file where the function call appears (up to 256 bytes).

params.name: data.line_number
params.description: The line number in file_name where the function call appears.

params.name: data.column_number
params.description: The column number where the function call appears, if available. This is important in JavaScript because of its anonymous functions.

params.name: data.load_module
params.description: The binary module from where the code was loaded.

params.name: data.source_version
params.description: The version of the deployed source code (up to 128 bytes).
